text:
Is there some reason why they keep closing early, and why they don't give any warning until they're 15 mins from closing? I visited few days ago and was told they were suddenly closing at 18:00 when they were meant to close at 19:00, then just yesterday it was 18:30 when they were supposed to be closing at 20:00. No time change is mentioned on the app or Google Maps, they don't put any poster on the door, they just tell you when you've got 15 mins left.

I'd put it down to the festive period, but this happened months ago at another Starbucks. Really annoying as when I visit, I'm usually there for whole day until closing time in order to get some work done.

Additionally, why is it that parents think a Starbucks is a playground for their kids to run up and down and make a lot of noise? This is just disruptive for those trying to get some work done, and those just trying to relax for 15 mins. Also really annoying.

text:
My recent visit to the Starbucks in Streatham left me with mixed feelings. On the positive side, I must commend the staff for their excellent service. From the moment I walked in, they were attentive, friendly, and efficient, making me feel welcome and valued as a customer. The prompt service truly enhanced my experience.

However, the one glaring downside was the condition of the seating area, particularly the sofas. They were visibly dirty and emitted an unpleasant odor, which detracted from the overall ambiance of the café. It's clear that these sofas are in need of a thorough cleaning, as they don't align with the otherwise high standards I've come to expect from Starbucks.

In summary, while the service at this Streatham Starbucks was exceptional, the cleanliness of the seating area, especially the sofas, left much to be desired. I hope the management takes this feedback into consideration and takes steps to address this issue, as it could significantly improve the overall customer experience.

text:
It being so large is the best thing about it. But the seating is truly awful. Incredibly low, uncomfortable chairs and tables. Unnatural to sit at. It must be a tactic so people don’t stay too long. I really hope they improve this most of all, but suspect they (management) won’t or aren’t allowed.

It’s a bit dirty too, but that’s just because the poor staff are so busy, particularly with delivery orders. I really hope they’re compensated well. Also the lighting along the right hand side shines directly into the faces of the people sitting against the wall.

The coffee cups are ridiculously too big and heavy, which make them uncomfortable to hold. And I think always too milky because of the size of the mugs. I dislike the wooden spoons in my hot drink, too, but I think might be an autistic thing. It can’t be to prevent waste, right? Since the wooden spoons are still disposable. I’d rather normal crockery.

Ordering is awkward too. Collecting it yourself but they never asked for my name or gave a number or anything. I kept going back up as my coffee order was very general and got confused with another, and my food was pastry at a different time. I didn’t want to leave my bag and coat, or otherwise lose my seat and table.
